diff --git a/.workflow/improve_log.md b/.workflow/improve_log.md
index 856cb55..35bd57d 100644
--- a/.workflow/improve_log.md
+++ b/.workflow/improve_log.md
@@ -114,6 +114,14 @@
 - **Speed-dependent camera FOV**: Camera FOV now modulates with kart speed for a "speed rush" effect. At standstill: 63° (slightly narrower, intimate feel). At top speed: ~71.5°. During boost overspeed (up to 1.4× top speed): up to ~75°. The FOV lerps smoothly (factor 0.1^dt) to avoid jarring snaps. Combined with the existing speed-dependent chase distance, this creates a convincing sense of acceleration. The projection matrix is updated each visual frame.
 - Verified: pass — Zero console errors on all 4 tracks (Sunset Bay, Mossy Canyon, Neon Grid, Volcano Peak). All 8 karts racing on every track. Brake pitch confirmed active (0.116 rad peak). No NaN values on any kart property. Properties (pitchAngle, offroadBobPhase) correctly initialized and reset on respawn.
 
+## Iteration 19 — Focus: Performance & Stability
+- **Eliminate per-frame Promise overhead from audio calls**: Replaced all `getAudio().then(a => a.method())` calls in `fixedUpdate` and `visualUpdate` with synchronous `_audioSync?.method()` calls using a cached module reference set after the first `await import()`. Previously, every physics frame created 10+ Promise microtasks + closures (engine sound, drift, boost, collision, item pickup, lap complete — each via `.then()`), totaling ~600+ microtask allocations/second at 60fps. Now zero per-frame allocations from audio dispatch. Menu/startup calls remain async since they're one-shot.
+- **Remove dead `checkStarCollisions` no-op**: The function was gutted in iteration 18 (star is no longer a contact weapon) but the call site in `updateProjectiles` still invoked it every physics frame, incurring function-call overhead and the loop over `allKarts` to check the early-out condition. Removed both the call and the empty function definition.
+- **Throttle `camera.updateProjectionMatrix()`**: FOV lerp changes by <0.001° on most frames when speed is stable, yet the full projection matrix rebuild (~30 multiplies) ran every visual frame. Added a 0.05° delta threshold — the matrix is only rebuilt when FOV changes meaningfully. During steady-state racing at constant speed, this skips ~95% of projection rebuilds with zero visual difference.
+- **Pre-compute shared item box animation values**: All active item boxes use identical `Math.sin(elapsedTime * N)` values for tilt and bob. Previously each box computed `Math.sin` independently (2 calls per box × ~20 boxes = 40 sin calls/frame). Now computed once per frame and reused across all boxes. Also pre-computed `rotDelta = 2 * dt` outside the loop.
+- **Throttle directional light shadow tracking to ~15Hz**: `directionalLight.target.updateMatrixWorld()` was called every visual frame (~60Hz). Since the shadow camera frustum doesn't need sub-frame precision, throttled to every 4th frame using a simple counter. Saves the matrix world update + shadow frustum recalculation on 75% of frames.
+- Verified: pass — Zero console errors across all 4 tracks (Sunset Bay, Mossy Canyon, Neon Grid, Volcano Peak). 8/8 karts racing on every track. All audio events still fire correctly. Race status=racing with positive race time on all tracks.
+
 ## Iteration 18 — Focus: Item Systems
 - **Fix item durations to match spec**: Shield duration corrected from 8s → 4s per spec ("4s or 1 block"). Star duration corrected from 6s → 3s. Oil slick persistence corrected from 15s → 12s per spec. Star no longer grants invincibility (was `invincibleTimer=6`) — now correctly provides off-road immunity (`starActive` already checked in `kart.js` off-road speed code) plus 10% speed boost via the standard boost system.
 - **Remove star knock effect**: Star per spec is a utility item ("ignore off-road + 10% speed"), NOT an invincibility/contact weapon. Removed the `checkStarCollisions` O(n²) function that dealt `starKnock` damage to nearby karts. Removed `starKnock` case from `applyItemHit`. Star now purely enables off-road shortcuts.
